  "title": "Machine Maintenance Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for troubleshooting, repairing, and servicing production machineries, equipment, systems, and infrastructures.</li>\n  <li>Responsible to ensure machinery and equipment runs smoothly and reliably. Minimize machine downtime.</li>\n  <li>In charge of performing Preventive and Predictive TPM as well as to monitor and control maintenance costs.</li>\n  <li>Taking charge of dealing with emergencies, unplanned problems, and repairs of machines breakdown</li>\n  <li>Responsible in using Root cause analysis tool to analyze the cause of the breakdown.</li>\n  <li>Maintains safe and clean working environment by complying with procedures, rules, and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Maintains continuity among work teams by documenting and communicating actions, irregularities, and continuing needs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Nitec in Electrical/ Electronics/ Mechanical Engineering</li>\n  <li>Min 3 years of working experience in Manufacturing industry</li>\n  <li>Must be able to work rotating shift</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com</strong></a><strong> </strong>or call <a href=\"tel:+(65) 6513 5697\"><strong>+(65) 6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd.<br>\nEA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
